{{Quote|She was something&hellip;''special''.|Dezono Qua|<ref name="TPTN5" />}}
'''Resa Greenbark''' was the daughter of [[Bomo Greenbark]], a [[Nosaurian/Legends|Nosaurian]] [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] in the [[New Plympto resistance (Imperial Period)|resistance movement]] on their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[New Plympto/Legends|New Plympto]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]]. During the final battle of the newly&ndash;[[Declaration of a New Order|instated]] [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Cleansing of New Plympto|cleansing]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], Resa and her mother [[Mesa Greenbark|Mesa]] were evacuated, only to be captured by the Empire and sent to [[Orvax IV]] along with the other evacuees as [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]]. Resa was then sold to [[Dezono Qua]] by [[Orso Meeto]], a transaction which Bomo discovered. From this, he was able to find Qua on [[Esseles/Legends|Esseles]]. When Qua was confronted by Bomo's companion, [[Dass Jennir]], he revealed that he had eaten the [[Youngling/Legends|child]], an act which earned Qua [[Death/Legends|death]] at Jennir's hands.

==Biography==
{{Quote|Mesa, my love, take good care care of our Resa.|Bomo Greenbark bids farewell to Mesa and Resa|<ref name="TPTN1" />}}
Resa Greenbark was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Nosaurian/Legends|Nosaurian]] from the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[New Plympto/Legends|New Plympto]]. She was an only [[Youngling/Legends|child]]<ref name="BH4">[[Dark Times 16|''Dark Times'' 16]]</ref> and the daughter of [[Mesa Greenbark|Mesa]] and [[Bomo Greenbark]].<ref name="TPTN1" /> Her father Bomo was a [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] in the [[New Plympto resistance (Imperial Period)|Nosaurian resistance]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] and [[Cleansing of New Plympto|fought]] against the newly&ndash;[[Declaration of a New Order|formed]] [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]].<ref name="ITU1">[[Republic 79|''Republic'' 79]]</ref> The resistance made a last stand at [[Half-Axe Pass]] and held off the Imperial forces while those Nosaurians not involved in the fighting were evacuated. Bomo oversaw the evacuation of Resa and Mesa on the last of the [[Transport/Legends|transports]] but, having a duty to return to the fighting, was unable to join them despite Resa's pleas. The evacuees were taken to [[Cadgel Meadows]] where Mesa and Resa hoped to take a [[Starship/Legends|ship]] to [[Sullust/Legends|Sullust]], but Imperial forces at the [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] captured all of the evacuees.<ref name="TPTN1" /> Deeming them inadequate to add to the workforce, the Empire took them to [[Orvax IV]] to be sold for a profit as [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]].<ref name="TPTN2">[[Dark Times 2|''Dark Times'' 2]]</ref>

On Orvax IV, Resa was taken to be sold by a [[Chagrian/Legends|Chagrian]] slaver, [[Orso Meeto]]. This resulted in Mesa being [[Death/Legends|killed]] when she attempted to stop a number of slavers from subsequently taking her daughter. Meeto sold the Nosaurian youngling to [[Dezono Qua]], a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Noble/Legends|noble]] on [[Esseles/Legends|Esseles]]. Bomo and the crew of the ''[[Uhumele]]'', who had rescued him and his companion [[Dass Jennir]] from New Plympto, [[Mission to Orvax IV|arrived]] on Orvax IV mere [[Standard hour/Legends|hours]] later, too late to find Resa.<ref name="TPTN4">[[Dark Times 4|''Dark Times'' 4]]</ref>

In Qua's fortified [[Qua family's villa|villa]] on Esseles, Resa was killed for [[E-10]]&mdash;Qua's [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]]&mdash;to prepare her as a meal for the noble, as was always done with the young slaves he purchased. However, unbeknownst to him, the crew of the ''Uhumele'' had located Resa's buyer and [[Assault on Dezono Qua's villa|attacked]] the villa soon after Resa had been eaten. Jennir confronted Qua as he attempted to escape, with Bomo and the other crewmembers arriving shortly before Qua revealed that he had eaten Resa. Jennir then shot and killed the noble with his [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] to spare Bomo from suffering the after-effects of killing Qua himself.<ref name="TPTN5" />

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Papa! Come with us!|Resa pleading with her father|<ref name="TPTN1" />}}
Resa was much loved by her parents, with her mother even dying to try and stop Resa being taken away from her.<ref name="TPTN4" /> Bomo, Resa's father, wore a [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojector]] around his neck that displayed a [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]] of Resa. During the evacuation, Resa begged her father multiple times to go with her, but Bomo refused, having a duty to stay. This upset Resa, but she was comforted by her father when he showed her his hologram of her.<ref name="TPTN1" />

==Behind the scenes==
Resa's only appearance was in the [[Dark Times 1|''Dark Times'' 1]], the first issue of the [[Star Wars: Dark Times: The Path to Nowhere|first story arc]] in the ''[[Star Wars: Dark Times]]'' [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series,<ref name="TPTN1" /> which was released on [[November 8]], [[2006]].<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54075/star_wars_dark_times_2006_1|text=Star Wars: Dark Times (2006) #1}}</ref> The issue was written by Mic Harrison,<ref name="TPTN1" /> a pen name of [[Randy Stradley]],<ref name="Insider 127">{{InsiderCite|127|Blaster}}</ref> and illustrated by [[Douglas Wheatley]].<ref name="TPTN1" />

